{
  "texts": [
    "After identifying courtship frames (see 'Courtship experiments'), we split these frames into train, validation and test sets.",
    "To form a test set for a given LC type (or control), we randomly selected 3-s windows across all flies until we had 15 min of data (27,000 frames).",
    "Selecting windows instead of randomly choosing time frames ensured that no frame in the visual input of the test data overlapped with any training frames.",
    "For control sessions, after selecting the test set, we also randomly sampled from the remaining frames to form a validation set (27,000 frames) in the same way as we did for the test set; the validation set was used for hyperparameter choices and early stopping.",
    "All remaining frames were used for training."
  ]
}